  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7033 sitting just above the max positive gamma wall at 7030 (13.8B), dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls stacked between 7000-7050 suggests dealers will aggressively fade any breakout attempts above 7035, while the wall_break event indicates we've likely punched through a key level that's now triggering rebalancing flows. Watch 7030 as the critical pivot - failure to hold above it should trigger dealer buying back toward 7000, while sustained move above 7035 faces another 12.6B gamma wall.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect heavy two-way action between 7000-7050 with dealers capping upside moves.",
